The paper proposes a transfer learning framework using decision forests, which is a popular machine learning technique for classification and regression tasks. The paper focuses on improving the performance of the model on a target domain by refining the model learned on a source domain. This is a common problem in machine learning, and the proposed methods are likely to be of interest to researchers in several sub-fields of computer science. Based on the abstract, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
